ngs:\n\n- code.storage Git Sync can mirror public GitHub repositories without GitHub App\n  credentials through public mode, then refresh with `pullUpstream()`\n  ([Public GitHub Sync](https://code.[REDACTED:entropy]),\n  [Git Sync docs](https://code.storage/docs/guides/integrations)).\n- code.storage also supports generic HTTPS Git sync for GitLab, Bitbucket,\n  Gitea, Forgejo, Codeberg, SourceHut, and similar hosts\n  ([Generic HTTPS Git sync](https://code.storage/changelog/generic-https-git-sync)).\n- code.storage exposes normal Git operations over HTTPS: `git clone`,\n  `git fetch`, `git pull`, and `git push` against JWT-authenticated remotes\n  ([Git Operations](https://code.storage/docs/guides/git-operations)).\n- The docs prove Git remote behavior, but do not prove that Git Sync mirrors\n  arbitrary custom refs such as `refs/meta/main`. That needs a direct spike with\n  `git ls-remote <code-storage-remote> 'refs/meta/*'`.\n- No code.storage docs found indicate FUSE, mounted repo directories, or any\n  mechanism that makes a remote repository appear as a local path to a server\n  process.\n\nImplication: Pierre/code.storage is a good optional upstream for a generator\nservice's local scratch repository. It is not the generator runtime.\n\n### Deployment Runtime\n\nVercel-style Next.js functions are a poor fit for Agent Trail generation.\n\nRelevant findings:\n\n- Vercel Functions have a read-only filesystem plus writable `/tmp` scratch\n  space capped at 500 MB\n  ([Vercel runtimes](https://vercel.com/docs/functions/runtimes)).\n- Vercel Node functions have bounded duration, bundle size, memory, and file\n  descriptor limits\n  ([Vercel limits](https://vercel.com/docs/functions/limitations)).\n- Vercel recommends object storage for persisted writes from functions\n  ([Vercel files guide](https://vercel.[REDACTED:entropy])).\n- Next can run native/server-only packages, but server dependencies are bundled\n  by default; packages using Node-specific behavior may need\n  `serverExternalPackages`\n  ([Next serverExternalPackages](https://nextjs.[REDACTED:entropy])).\n- Edge runtime is off the table for generation because it does not support the\n  needed Node APIs\n  ([Next Edge Runtime](https://nextjs.org/docs/app/api-reference/edge)).\n## gitbutler/workspace\n?? agent-trail.md\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-24T16:13:18.672Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}